13 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Study of offender re-entry services. (1) For the interim following the
14 69th legislative session, the law and justice interim committee shall study issues related to the provision of
15 offender re-entry services provided by the state.
16 (2) At a minimum, the study must include a consideration of the following:
17 (a) costs and benefits of offender individual re-entry services;
18 (b) re-entry programs successful in other states; and
19 (c) impacts of re-entry services on recidivism in Montana and in other states.
20 (3) The law and justice interim committee shall complete the study by September 15, 2026, and
21 report its findings and recommendations, including potential legislation, to the 70th legislature and to the judicial
22 branch, law enforcement, and justice interim budget committee.
23 (4) The law and justice interim committee shall invite the members of the judicial branch, law
24 enforcement, and justice interim budget committee to each of its meetings to participate in the study.
25
